title: Brookhaven officer hit during standoff at apartment complex
text:
BROOKHAVEN, Miss. (AP) - Brookhaven Police are involved in a standoff with a man barricaded inside a Brookhaven Apartment complex.
An officer suffered an injury Monday from the gunfire, but it is unclear if he was hit by a bullet or shrapnel. Multiple media outlets report his injuries are not life-threatening.
The Mississippi Highway Patrol SWAT Team has been sent to the scene.
Details about what sparked the standoff have not been released.
